
Changes valhalla such that it is possible to say 'OK to All' when ..db
files are missing.

Fri Apr 18 13:49:37 METDST 1997 / jlk
-------------------------------------

Added stackbrowser functionality as a supplement to the current stack viewer.

This stackbrowser is not final, since there is a need for more
elaborate functionality to make the stackbrowser a true
manifestication of the stack.  However, the current version is a good
first shot at a true stackbrowser.

The advanced (lacking) functionality is, that whenever code and
objects needs to be shown, there needs to be implemented a test for,
whether this code/object is on (one of) the stack(s).  And if so, the
code/object should be shown in that particular stackbrowser (now it
will be shown in a separate window).

Mon Mar 31 22:20:03 MET 1997 / jlk
----------------------------------

1) Made sure, that all output (error messages) are shown in dialog
boxes, and not just written on screen.  All these messages are
converted into the new exception otherError in processInterface.

2) changed the strategy for testing for source code modifications
since last linking of the executable from using scanning the
dependency graph (slow) to using the file info in the executable by
using the debugger function scanObjectFileInfo.

3) removed valhallaMachineName, and now uses betaenv.machine_type instead.

4) Uses DBmanager operation 'slotNameToGroups' to find the fragment
group defining the program-fragment.  This implies, that Valhalla now
can find the source code, even when the executable have been remaned
and moved in the file structure.

Wed Feb 26 11:07:49 MET 1997 / datpete
--------------------------------------

1) Fixed error in betasematt in betaast/v5.1: The
   change made in index.bet for originoff was not made in
   betasematt. 
   Now objectviews also work correct in linux valhalla.

2) Introduced use of BUILD instead of MAKE in valhalla code.

3) Reintroduced pwrite for sgi - the libraryversion does not seem to work
   for breakpoint setting.

Wed Feb 19 15:26:58 MET 1997 / datpete
--------------------------------------

Fixed stupid bug in private/binarystreambody:
rep.R's initial range is now 2 instead of 1.
This prevents BinaryStreamFragRestore from destroying
NEXT object in heap, since it starts by reading 2 longs
without range check.

This error was not visible on RISC's since the
8-byte alignment on objects on all these platforms ensures,
that there is actually room for the 2 longs, even though 
the initial range was only 1!

Linux valhalla now sems to work!

